According to [[Constitution of Myanmar]], the '''Constitutional Tribunal of Myanmar''' ({{lang-my|နိုင်ငံတော်ဖွဲ့စည်းပုံအခြေခံဥပဒေဆိုင်ရာခုံရုံး}}) was founded on 31 March 2011. Its headquarters is located in Office No. 54, [[Ottarathiri Township]], Nay Pyi Taw City, [[Myanmar]]. There is one chairperson and eight members on the Tribunal, who serve five year terms. Members of the tribunal are elected proportionally by the [[President of Burma|President]], [[Pyithu Hluttaw]], and [[Amyotha Hluttaw]]. The members of the Constitutional Tribunal are all required to be legal experts.
