A '''Wigmore chart''' (commonly referred to as '''Wigmorean analysis''') is a [[information graphics|graphical method]] for the analysis of [[law|legal]] [[evidence (law)|evidence]] in [[trial (law)|trial]]s, developed by [[John Henry Wigmore]].<ref>Anderson ''et al.'' (2005), Chapter 5</ref><ref>Wigmore (1913), (1937)</ref> It is an early form of the modern [[belief network]].<ref>Kadane & Schum (1996) ''pp''66-76</ref>

